{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775841547739,"sessionID":"ses_28798c033ffeiLKSjmHjP0bQ2x","part":{"id":"prt_d786789e1001oyh1HS63wU3KcJ","messageID":"msg_d786780da001xcnqn4y732BFFE","sessionID":"ses_28798c033ffeiLKSjmHjP0bQ2x","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AgentCube CRD Type Definitions\n2: \n3: This proposal defines the Custom Resource Definition (CRD) types for the AgentCube project.\n4: \n5: ---\n6: \n7: # AR-001 — CRD AgentRuntime 类型定义\n8: \n9: ## Purpose\n10: \n11: Define the `AgentRuntime` Custom Resource Definition (CRD) types in `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1` to enable Kubernetes-native sandbox orchestration for AI agent workloads. This work establishes the core API surface — `AgentRuntime`, `AgentRuntimeSpec`, `AgentRuntimeStatus`, and supporting shared types — that the Workload Manager controller and generated `client-go` library consume.\n12: \n13: ## Scope\n14: \n15: ### In scope\n16: \n17: | Item | Detail |\n18: |------|--------|\n19: | **Package** | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1` |\n20: | **API group** | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` |\n21: | **Version** | `v1alpha1` |\n22: | **Types defined** | `AgentRuntime`, `AgentRuntimeList`, `AgentRuntimeSpec`, `AgentRuntimeStatus`, `TargetPort`, `ProtocolType`, `SandboxTemplate` |\n23: | **Scheme registration** | `groupversion_info.go`, `register.go` — `GroupVersion`, `SchemeBuilder`, `AddToScheme`, kind constants, `Resource()` helper |\n24: | **Kubebuilder markers** | `+genclient`, `+k8s:deepcopy-gen`, `+kubebuilder:object:root=true`, `+kubebuilder:subresource:status`, `+kubebuilder:resource:scope=Namespaced`, `+kubebuilder:printcolumn`, validation/default markers |\n25: | **Code generation** | `controller-gen crd` → `manifests/charts/base/crds/`; `controller-gen object` → `zz_generated.deepcopy.go`; `k8s.io/code-generator` → `client-go/` |\n26: | **Generated client surface** | `AgentRuntimeInterface` (Create/Update/UpdateStatus/Delete/DeleteCollection/Get/List/Watch/Patch), `AgentRuntimeInformer`, `AgentRuntimeLister` |\n27: \n28: ### Out of scope\n29: \n30: - `CodeInterpreter` CRD types (separate AR)\n31: - Workload Manager HTTP API routes and handlers\n32: - Reconciler/controller logic\n33: - Helm chart CRD YAML rendering (consumes output, not produced here)\n34: - RBAC / ServiceAccount definitions\n35: \n36: ## Design\n37: \n38: ### File layout\n39: \n40: | File | Role |\n41: |------|------|\n42: | `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/groupversion_info.go` | `+groupName` marker, `GroupVersion`, `SchemeBuilder`, `AddToScheme` |\n43: | `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/register.go` | Kind constants (`AgentRuntimeKind`, `AgentRuntimeListKind`, `AgentRuntimeGroupVersionKind`), `SchemeGroupVersion`, `Resource()` helper |\n44: | `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agent_type.go` | `AgentRuntime`, `AgentRuntimeList`, `AgentRuntimeSpec`, `AgentRuntimeStatus` |\n45: | `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/shared_types.go` | `TargetPort`, `ProtocolType`, `SandboxTemplate` |\n46: | `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/zz_generated.deepcopy.go` | Auto-generated by `controller-gen object` |\n47: \n48: ### Type definitions\n49: \n50: **`AgentRuntime`** — namespaced CRD with `status` subresource:\n51: \n52: ```go\n53: // +genclient\n54: // +k8s:deepcopy-gen:interfaces=k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime.Object\n55: // +kubebuilder:object:root=true\n56: // +kubebuilder:subresource:status\n57: // +kubebuilder:resource:scope=Namespaced\n58: // +kubebuilder:printcolumn:name=\"Age\",type=\"date\",JSONPath=\".metadata.creationTimestamp\"\n59: type AgentRuntime struct {\n60:     metav1.TypeMeta   `json:\",inline\"`\n61:     metav1.ObjectMeta `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n62:     Spec   AgentRuntimeSpec   `json:\"spec\"`\n63:     Status AgentRuntimeStatus `json:\"status,omitempty\"`\n64: }\n65: ```\n66: \n67: **`AgentRuntimeSpec`** — sandbox template and session constraints:\n68: \n69: ```go\n70: type AgentRuntimeSpec struct {\n71:     Ports []TargetPort `json:\"targetPort\"`\n72:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n73:     Template *SandboxTemplate `json:\"podTemplate\" protobuf:\"bytes,1,opt,name=podTemplate\"`\n74:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n75:     // +kubebuilder:default=\"15m\"\n76:     SessionTimeout *metav1.Duration `json:\"sessionTimeout,omitempty\" protobuf:\"bytes,2,opt,name=sessionTimeout\"`\n77:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n78:     // +kubebuilder:default=\"8h\"\n79:     MaxSessionDuration *metav1.Duration `json:\"maxSessionDuration,omitempty\" protobuf:\"bytes,3,opt,name=maxSessionDuration\"`\n80: }\n81: ```\n82: \n83: **`AgentRuntimeStatus`** — condition-based status:\n84: \n85: ```go\n86: type AgentRuntimeStatus struct {\n87:     // +optional\n88:     Conditions []metav1.Condition `json:\"conditions,omitempty\"`\n89: }\n90: ```\n91: \n92: **`AgentRuntimeList`**:\n93: \n94: ```go\n95: // +k8s:deepcopy-gen:interfaces=k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime.Object\n96: // +kubebuilder:object:root=true\n97: type AgentRuntimeList struct {\n98:     metav1.TypeMeta `json:\",inline\"`\n99:     metav1.ListMeta `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n100:     Items           []AgentRuntime `json:\"items\"`\n101: }\n102: ```\n103: \n104: **Shared types** (`TargetPort`, `ProtocolType`, `SandboxTemplate`):\n105: \n106: ```go\n107: type ProtocolType string\n108: \n109: const (\n110:     ProtocolTypeHTTP  ProtocolType = \"HTTP\"\n111:     ProtocolTypeHTTPS ProtocolType = \"HTTPS\"\n112: )\n113: \n114: type TargetPort struct {\n115:     // +optional\n116:     PathPrefix *string `json:\"pathPrefix,omitempty\"`\n117:     // +optional\n118:     Name *string `json:\"name,omitempty\"`\n119:     Port uint32 `json:\"port\"`\n120:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n121:     // +kubebuilder:default=HTTP\n122:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Enum=HTTP;HTTPS\n123:     Protocol ProtocolType `json:\"protocol\"`\n124: }\n125: \n126: type SandboxTemplate struct {\n127:     // +optional\n128:     Labels map[string]string `json:\"labels,omitempty\"`\n129:     // +optional\n130:     Annotations map[string]string `json:\"annotations,omitempty\"`\n131:     Spec corev1.PodSpec `json:\"spec\"`\n132: }\n133: ```\n134: \n135: ### Scheme registration\n136: \n137: **`groupversion_info.go`**:\n138: \n139: ```go\n140: // +groupName=runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\n141: package v1alpha1\n142: \n143: var (\n144:     GroupVersion = schema.GroupVersion{Group: \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\", Version: \"v1alpha1\"}\n145:     SchemeBuilder = &scheme.Builder{GroupVersion: GroupVersion}\n146:     AddToScheme = SchemeBuilder.AddToScheme\n147: )\n148: ```\n149: \n150: **`register.go`**:\n151: \n152: ```go\n153: var (\n154:     AgentRuntimeKind             = \"AgentRuntime\"\n155:     AgentRuntimeListKind         = \"AgentRuntimeList\"\n156:     AgentRuntimeGroupVersionKind = GroupVersion.WithKind(\"AgentRuntime\")\n157: )\n158: \n159: var SchemeGroupVersion = GroupVersion\n160: \n161: func Resource(resource string) schema.GroupVersionResource {\n162:     return GroupVersion.WithResource(resource)\n163: }\n164: ```\n165: \n166: ### Code generation pipeline\n167: \n168: ```\n169: controller-gen crd  → manifests/charts/base/crds/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_agentruntimes.yaml\n170: controller-gen object → pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/zz_generated.deepcopy.go\n171: k8s.io/code-generator → client-go/ (clientset, informers, listers, fakes)\n172: ```\n173: \n174: Invocation: `make gen-all` → `generate` (controller-gen) + `gen-client` (`hack/update-codegen.sh`).\n175: \n176: ## Impact analysis\n177: \n178: ### Files created\n179: \n180: | File | Lines (est.) |\n181: |------|-------------|\n182: | `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/groupversion_info.go` | ~25 |\n183: | `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/register.go` | ~25 |\n184: | `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agent_type.go` | ~60 |\n185: | `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/shared_types.go` | ~45 |\n186: \n187: ### Files generated (not hand-edited)\n188: \n189: | File | Tool |\n190: |------|------|\n191: | `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/zz_generated.deepcopy.go` | `controller-gen object` |\n192: | `manifests/charts/base/crds/*.yaml` | `controller-gen crd` |\n193: | `client-go/` (entire tree) | `k8s.io/code-generator` |\n194: \n195: ### Downstream consumers\n196: \n197: | Consumer | Dependency |\n198: |----------|-----------|\n199: | `client-go` typed client | Imports `runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime` / `AgentRuntimeList` for CRUD operations |\n200: | `client-go` informers/listers | Uses `AgentRuntimeInformer`, `AgentRuntimeLister` built from these types |\n201: | Workload Manager controller | Imports types for sandbox lifecycle reconciliation |\n202: | Helm chart CRDs | Rendered YAML consumed by `kubectl apply` / Helm install |\n203: | Fake clients | `client-go/.../fake/` test doubles for unit testing |\n204: \n205: ### Breaking change risk\n206: \n207: - **Low**: This is a greenfield type definition. No existing runtime behavior is modified.\n208: - **Future**: Adding required fields to `AgentRuntimeSpec` after initial release will require CRD version bump (`v1alpha1` → `v1alpha2`) and conversion webhook.\n209: \n210: ## Alternatives considered\n211: \n212: ### 1. Standalone CRD YAML (no Go types)\n213: \n214: **Approach**: Write CRD manifests directly as YAML without Go type definitions.\n215: \n216: **Rejected because**: AgentCube uses Go controllers (Workload Manager) that require typed Go structs for serialization, validation, and scheme registration. YAML-only CRDs would force manual JSON unmarshaling and lose compile-time type safety.\n217: \n218: ### 2. Kubebuilder/controller-runtime scaffolding\n219: \n220: **Approach**: Use `kubebuilder create api` to scaffold the full controller + CRD project structure.\n221: \n222: **Rejected because**: AgentCube's Workload Manager is a Gin-based HTTP service, not a controller-runtime manager. The project uses `controller-gen` for type/code generation only, without the controller-runtime manager scaffolding. Adopting Kubebuilder would introduce an unnecessary runtime dependency and project structure mismatch.\n223: \n224: ### 3. Multi-version API from day one (`v1alpha1` + `v1beta1`)\n225: \n226: **Approach**: Define two API versions simultaneously with a conversion webhook.\n227: \n228: **Rejected because**: The project is pre-GA with no existing users. A single `v1alpha1` version is sufficient for initial development. Adding versions and conversion webhooks adds operational complexity without current benefit.\n229: \n230: ### 4. Embed full `corev1.PodTemplateSpec` instead of custom `SandboxTemplate`\n231: \n232: **Approach**: Use `corev1.PodTemplateSpec` directly in `AgentRuntimeSpec` rather than the lighter `SandboxTemplate` wrapper.\n233: \n234: **Rejected because**: `SandboxTemplate` provides a controlled surface — optional `labels`/`annotations` maps with a required embedded `corev1.PodSpec` — while keeping the CRD schema focused on what AgentCube manages. Full `PodTemplateSpec` would expose `ObjectMeta` fields that are not relevant to sandbox template configuration.\n235: \n236: ## Dependencies\n237: \n238: | Dependency | Version | Purpose |\n239: |------------|---------|---------|\n240: | `k8s.io/apimachinery` | `v0.34.1` | `metav1.TypeMeta`, `metav1.ObjectMeta`, `metav1.Duration`, `metav1.Condition`, `schema.GroupVersion` |\n241: | `k8s.io/api` | `v0.34.1` | `corev1.PodSpec` embedded in `SandboxTemplate` |\n242: | `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime` | `v0.22.2` | `scheme.Builder` for scheme registration |\n243: | `controller-gen` | `v0.17.2` | CRD YAML and deepcopy generation |\n244: | `k8s.io/code-generator` | `v0.34.1` | client-go library generation |\n245: \n246: ## Verification\n247: \n248: ```bash\n249: # Generate CRD YAML, deepcopy, and client-go\n250: make gen-all\n251: \n252: # Verify no diff (all generated files committed)\n253: make gen-check\n254: \n255: # Validate CRD schema\n256: kubectl apply -f manifests/charts/base/crds/ --dry-run=server\n257: ```\n258: \n259: ---\n260: \n261: # AR-002 — CRD CodeInterpreter 类型定义\n262: \n263: ## Purpose\n264: \n265: Define the `CodeInterpreter` Custom Resource Definition (CRD) types in `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1` to enable Kubernetes-native code execution environments for AI agents. The CodeInterpreter CRD represents a specialized sandbox instance designed for executing code snippets safely. This work extends the existing `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` API group with the `CodeInterpreter` type alongside `AgentRuntime`, sharing the same scheme registration and code generation pipeline.\n266: \n267: ## Scope\n268: \n269: ### In scope\n270: \n271: | Item | Detail |\n272: |------|--------|\n273: | **Package** | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1` |\n274: | **API group** | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` |\n275: | **Version** | `v1alpha1` |\n276: | **Types defined** | `CodeInterpreter`, `CodeInterpreterList`, `CodeInterpreterSpec`, `CodeInterpreterStatus`, `CodeInterpreterPhase` |\n277: | **Scheme registration** | Update `register.go` to include `CodeInterpreter` and `CodeInterpreterList` in `addKnownTypes` |\n278: | **Kubebuilder markers** | `+genclient`, `+k8s:deepcopy-gen`, `+kubebuilder:object:root=true`, `+kubebuilder:subresource:status`, `+kubebuilder:resource:scope=Namespaced`, `+kubebuilder:printcolumn`, validation markers |\n279: | **Code generation** | `controller-gen crd` → `manifests/charts/base/crds/`; `controller-gen object` → `zz_generated.deepcopy.go`; `k8s.io/code-generator` → `client-go/` |\n280: | **Generated client surface** | `CodeInterpreterInterface` (Create/Update/UpdateStatus/Delete/DeleteCollection/Get/List/Watch/Patch), `CodeInterpreterInformer`, `CodeInterpreterLister` |\n281: \n282: ### Out of scope\n283: \n284: - Workload Manager HTTP API routes and handlers for CodeInterpreter\n285: - Reconciler/controller logic specific to CodeInterpreter lifecycle\n286: - Helm chart CRD YAML rendering (consumes output, not produced here)\n287: - RBAC / ServiceAccount definitions\n288: - Multi-version API or conversion webhooks\n289: \n290: ## Design\n291: \n292: ### File layout\n293: \n294: | File | Role |\n295: |------|------|\n296: | `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go` | `CodeInterpreter`, `CodeInterpreterList`, `CodeInterpreterSpec`, `CodeInterpreterStatus`, `CodeInterpreterPhase` type definitions |\n297: | `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/register.go` | Updated to include `CodeInterpreter` and `CodeInterpreterList` in scheme registration |\n298: | `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/zz_generated.deepcopy.go` | Auto-generated by `controller-gen object` (includes CodeInterpreter types) |\n299: \n300: ### Type definitions\n301: \n302: **`CodeInterpreterPhase`** — enum for lifecycle phases:\n303: \n304: ```go\n305: // CodeInterpreterPhase represents the current phase of a CodeInterpreter.\n306: // +kubebuilder:validation:Enum=Pending;Running;Succeeded;Failed\n307: // +kubebuilder:validation:Type=string\n308: type CodeInterpreterPhase string\n309: \n310: const (\n311:     CodeInterpreterPhasePending   CodeInterpreterPhase = \"Pending\"\n312:     CodeInterpreterPhaseRunning   CodeInterpreterPhase = \"Running\"\n313:     CodeInterpreterPhaseSucceeded CodeInterpreterPhase = \"Succeeded\"\n314:     CodeInterpreterPhaseFailed    CodeInterpreterPhase = \"Failed\"\n315: )\n316: ```\n317: \n318: **`CodeInterpreter`** — namespaced CRD with `status` subresource:\n319: \n320: ```go\n321: // +genclient\n322: // +k8s:deepcopy-gen:interfaces=k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime.Object\n323: // +kubebuilder:object:root=true\n324: // +kubebuilder:subresource:status\n325: // +kubebuilder:resource:scope=Namespaced,path=codeinterpreters,shortName=ci;cis,singular=codeinterpreter,categories={agentcube,all}\n326: // +kubebuilder:printcolumn:name=\"Phase\",type=string,JSONPath=`.status.phase`,description=\"Current phase\"\n327: // +kubebuilder:printcolumn:name=\"Age\",type=date,JSONPath=`.metadata.creationTimestamp`,description=\"Time since creation\"\n328: \n329: // CodeInterpreter is the Schema for the codeinterpreters API.\n330: // A CodeInterpreter represents a specialized sandbox for executing code snippets.\n331: type CodeInterpreter struct {\n332:     metav1.TypeMeta   `json:\",inline\"`\n333:     metav1.ObjectMeta `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n334:     Spec   CodeInterpreterSpec   `json:\"spec\"`\n335:     Status CodeInterpreterStatus `json:\"status,omitempty\"`\n336: }\n337: ```\n338: \n339: **`CodeInterpreterSpec`** — code execution configuration:\n340: \n341: ```go\n342: // CodeInterpreterSpec defines the desired state of CodeInterpreter.\n343: type CodeInterpreterSpec struct {\n344:     // Image is the container image to use for the code interpreter sandbox.\n345:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n346:     // +kubebuilder:validation:MinLength=1\n347:     Image string `json:\"image\"`\n348: \n349:     // Resources defines the compute resources (CPU, memory) for the sandbox.\n350:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n351:     Resources *corev1.ResourceRequirements `json:\"resources,omitempty\"`\n352: \n353:     // Env defines environment variables to set in the sandbox container.\n354:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n355:     Env []corev1.EnvVar `json:\"env,omitempty\"`\n356: \n357:     // TimeoutSeconds specifies the maximum execution time (in seconds) for code snippets.\n358:     // If not specified, a default timeout will be applied.\n359:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n360:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Minimum=1\n361:     // +kubebuilder:default=300\n362:     TimeoutSeconds *int32 `json:\"timeoutSeconds,omitempty\"`\n363: \n364:     // MaxMemoryMB specifies the maximum memory (in MB) that code execution can use.\n365:     // This is a soft limit enforced within the sandbox.\n366:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n367:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Minimum=64\n368:     MaxMemoryMB *int32 `json:\"maxMemoryMB,omitempty\"`\n369: }\n370: ```\n371: \n372: **`CodeInterpreterStatus`** — execution status and results:\n373: \n374: ```go\n375: // CodeInterpreterStatus defines the observed state of CodeInterpreter.\n376: type CodeInterpreterStatus struct {\n377:     // Phase represents the current phase of the CodeInterpreter.\n378:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n379:     Phase CodeInterpreterPhase `json:\"phase,omitempty\"`\n380: \n381:     // Conditions represents the latest available observations of the CodeInterpreter's state.\n382:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n383:     Conditions []metav1.Condition `json:\"conditions,omitempty\"`\n384: \n385:     // SandboxID is the unique identifier of the created sandbox pod.\n386:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n387:     SandboxID string `json:\"sandboxId,omitempty\"`\n388: \n389:     // LastExecutionTime is the time of the last code execution.\n390:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n391:     LastExecutionTime *metav1.Time `json:\"lastExecutionTime,omitempty\"`\n392: \n393:     // ExecutionCount is the total number of code executions performed.\n394:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n395:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Minimum=0\n396:     ExecutionCount int32 `json:\"executionCount,omitempty\"`\n397: \n398:     // Message provides a human-readable description of the current status.\n399:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n400:     Message string `json:\"message,omitempty\"`\n401: \n402:     // Reason provides a brief reason for the current phase.\n403:     // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n404:     Reason string `json:\"reason,omitempty\"`\n405: }\n406: ```\n407: \n408: **`CodeInterpreterList`**:\n409: \n410: ```go\n411: // +k8s:deepcopy-gen:interfaces=k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime.Object\n412: // +kubebuilder:object:root=true\n413: \n414: // CodeInterpreterList contains a list of CodeInterpreter resources.\n415: type CodeInterpreterList struct {\n416:     metav1.TypeMeta `json:\",inline\"`\n417:     metav1.ListMeta `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n418:     Items           []CodeInterpreter `json:\"items\"`\n419: }\n420: ```\n421: \n422: ### Scheme registration\n423: \n424: **Updated `register.go`** — add CodeInterpreter types to scheme:\n425: \n426: ```go\n427: func addKnownTypes(scheme *runtime.Scheme) error {\n428:     scheme.AddKnownTypes(\n429:         SchemeGroupVersion,\n430:         &AgentRuntime{},\n431:         &AgentRuntimeList{},\n432:         &CodeInterpreter{},\n433:         &CodeInterpreterList{},\n434:     )\n435:     metav1.AddToGroupVersion(scheme, SchemeGroupVersion)\n436:     return nil\n437: }\n438: ```\n439: \n440: ### Code generation pipeline\n441: \n442: ```\n443: controller-gen crd  → manifests/charts/base/crds/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_codeinterpreters.yaml\n444: controller-gen object → pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/zz_generated.deepcopy.go\n445: k8s.io/code-generator → client-go/ (clientset, informers, listers, fakes including CodeInterpreter types)\n446: ```\n447: \n448: Invocation: `make gen-all` → `generate` (controller-gen) + `gen-client` (`hack/update-codegen.sh`).\n449: \n450: ## Impact analysis\n451: \n452: ### Files created\n453: \n454: | File | Lines (est.) |\n455: |------|-------------|\n456: | `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go` | ~120 |\n457: \n458: ### Files modified\n459: \n460: | File | Change |\n461: |------|--------|\n462: | `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/register.go` | Add `CodeInterpreter` and `CodeInterpreterList` to `addKnownTypes` |\n463: \n464: ### Files generated (not hand-edited)\n465: \n466: | File | Tool |\n467: |------|------|\n468: | `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/zz_generated.deepcopy.go` | `controller-gen object` (appends to existing) |\n469: | `manifests/charts/base/crds/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_codeinterpreters.yaml` | `controller-gen crd` |\n470: | `client-go/` (updated tree) | `k8s.io/code-generator` |\n471: \n472: ### Downstream consumers\n473: \n474: | Consumer | Dependency |\n475: |----------|-----------|\n476: | `client-go` typed client | Imports `runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter` / `CodeInterpreterList` for CRUD operations |\n477: | `client-go` informers/listers | Uses `CodeInterpreterInformer`, `CodeInterpreterLister` built from these types |\n478: | Workload Manager controller | Imports types for code interpreter lifecycle reconciliation |\n479: | Helm chart CRDs | Rendered YAML consumed by `kubectl apply` / Helm install |\n480: | Fake clients | `client-go/.../fake/` test doubles for unit testing |\n481: \n482: ### Breaking change risk\n483: \n484: - **Low**: This is a greenfield type definition that extends the existing API group. No existing runtime behavior is modified.\n485: - **Compatibility**: Shares the same `v1alpha1` version with `AgentRuntime`, ensuring consistent scheme registration and versioning.\n486: - **Future**: Adding required fields to `CodeInterpreterSpec` after initial release will require CRD version bump and conversion webhook.\n487: \n488: ## Alternatives considered\n489: \n490: ### 1. Extend AgentRuntime instead of separate CRD\n491: \n492: **Approach**: Add a `codeExecution` field to `AgentRuntimeSpec` to support code interpreter use cases within the existing AgentRuntime CRD.\n493: \n494: **Rejected because**: CodeInterpreter has distinct lifecycle semantics and configuration requirements (timeout, memory limits) compared to general agent runtimes. Separate CRDs allow independent RBAC, scheduling, and lifecycle management. The client-go library pattern (see spec) explicitly defines separate interfaces for `AgentRuntimes` and `CodeInterpreters`, indicating intentional separation.\n495: \n496: ### 2. Use v1beta1 version for CodeInterpreter\n497: \n498: **Approach**: Define CodeInterpreter in a new API version `v1beta1` while keeping AgentRuntime in `v1alpha1`.\n499: \n500: **Rejected because**: Both CRDs are being developed concurrently in the pre-GA phase. Using different versions adds unnecessary complexity for scheme registration, client generation, and version negotiation. A unified `v1alpha1` version is sufficient for initial development.\n501: \n502: ### 3. Embed full PodSpec in CodeInterpreterSpec\n503: \n504: **Approach**: Use `corev1.PodSpec` directly in `CodeInterpreterSpec` for maximum flexibility.\n505: \n506: **Rejected because**: Similar to AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter uses a controlled surface with focused fields (`Image`, `Resources`, `Env`, `TimeoutSeconds`, `MaxMemoryMB`). This simplifies the API and guides users toward code execution best practices without exposing irrelevant PodSpec fields.\n507: \n508: ### 4. Define CodeInterpreter in separate API group\n509: \n510: **Approach**: Create a new API group `code.agentcube.volcano.sh` for the CodeInterpreter CRD.\n511: \n512: **Rejected because**: CodeInterpreter and AgentRuntime share the same runtime concerns (sandbox lifecycle, resource management). Keeping them in the same `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` group simplifies scheme management and aligns with the client-go library structure where both types are accessed through the same `RuntimeV1alpha1Interface`.\n513: \n514: ## Dependencies\n515: \n516: | Dependency | Version | Purpose |\n517: |------------|---------|---------|\n518: | `k8s.io/apimachinery` | `v0.34.1` | `metav1.TypeMeta`, `metav1.ObjectMeta`, `metav1.Condition`, `metav1.Time`, `schema.GroupVersion` |\n519: | `k8s.io/api` | `v0.34.1` | `corev1.ResourceRequirements`, `corev1.EnvVar` |\n520: | `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime` | `v0.22.2` | `scheme.Builder` for scheme registration |\n521: | `controller-gen` | `v0.17.2` | CRD YAML and deepcopy generation |\n522: | `k8s.io/code-generator` | `v0.34.1` | client-go library generation |\n523: \n524: ## Verification\n525: \n526: ```bash\n527: # Generate CRD YAML, deepcopy, and client-go (includes CodeInterpreter)\n528: make gen-all\n529: \n530: # Verify no diff (all generated files committed)\n531: make gen-check\n532: \n533: # Validate CRD schema\n534: kubectl apply -f manifests/charts/base/crds/ --dry-run=server\n535: \n536: # Verify compilation includes new types\n537: go build ./pkg/apis/...\n538: \n539: # Run tests\n540: go test ./pkg/apis/...\n541: ```\n\n(End of file - total 541 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AgentCube CRD Type Definitions\n\nThis proposal defines the Custom Resource Definition (CRD) types for the AgentCube project.\n\n---\n\n# AR-001 — CRD AgentRuntime 类型定义\n\n## Purpose\n\nDefine the `AgentRuntime` Custom Resource Definition (CRD) types in `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1` to enable Kubernetes-native sandbox orchestration for AI agent workloads. This work establishes the core API surface — `AgentRuntime`, `AgentRuntimeSpec`, `AgentRuntimeStatus`, and supporting shared types — that the Workload Manager controller and generated `client-go` library consume.\n\n## Scope\n\n### In scope\n\n| Item | Detail |\n|------|--------|\n| **Package** | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1` |\n| **API group** | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775841547714,"end":1775841547736}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775841547742,"sessionID":"ses_28798c033ffeiLKSjmHjP0bQ2x","part":{"id":"prt_d78678db2001HtilG5pIn9OHDE","messageID":"msg_d786780da001xcnqn4y732BFFE","sessionID":"ses_28798c033ffeiLKSjmHjP0bQ2x","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:5","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-002 Design: CRD CodeInterpreter Type Definition\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: **AR ID:** AR-002  \n6: **Module:** `pkg/apis`  \n7: **Language:** Go  \n8: **Size:** Small  \n9: \n10: Define the Go type definitions for the `CodeInterpreter` Custom Resource Definition (CRD) under the API group `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`. The CodeInterpreter CRD represents a specialized sandbox for executing code snippets safely within Kubernetes.\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## Architecture\n15: \n16: ### High-Level Design\n17: \n18: The CodeInterpreter type extends the existing `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` API group alongside `AgentRuntime`, sharing the same scheme registration and code generation pipeline.\n19: \n20: ```\n21: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n22: │                    Kubernetes API Server                         │\n23: │  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n24: │  │  runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1                  │   │\n25: │  │  ┌─────────────┐  ┌─────────────────────────────────┐   │   │\n26: │  │  │ AgentRuntime│  │         CodeInterpreter         │   │   │\n27: │  │  │             │  │  ┌───────────────────────────┐  │   │   │\n28: │  │  │ ┌─────────┐ │  │  │ CodeInterpreterSpec       │  │   │   │\n29: │  │  │ │ Image   │ │  │  │ - Image (required)        │  │   │   │\n30: │  │  │ │ Resources│ │  │  │ - Language (enum)         │  │   │   │\n31: │  │  │ │ Ports   │ │  │  │ - Resources (optional)    │  │   │   │\n32: │  │  │ │ ...     │ │  │  │ - TimeoutSeconds          │  │   │   │\n33: │  │  │ └─────────┘ │  │  │ - MaxMemoryMB             │  │   │   │\n34: │  │  │             │  │  │ - Env                     │  │   │   │\n35: │  │  │ ┌─────────┐ │  │  └───────────────────────────┘  │   │   │\n36: │  │  │ │ Status  │ │  │  ┌───────────────────────────┐  │   │   │\n37: │  │  │ │ Phase   │ │  │  │ CodeInterpreterStatus     │  │   │   │\n38: │  │  │ │ ...     │ │  │  │ - Phase (enum)            │  │   │   │\n39: │  │  │ └─────────┘ │  │  │ - Conditions              │  │   │   │\n40: │  │  └─────────────┘  │  │ - SandboxID               │  │   │   │\n41: │  │                   │  │ - ExecutionCount          │  │   │   │\n42: │  │                   │  └───────────────────────────┘  │   │   │\n43: │  │                   └─────────────────────────────────┘   │   │\n44: │  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n45: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n46:                               │\n47:                               ▼\n48: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n49: │                    Generated client-go                          │\n50: │  ┌─────────────────┐  ┌─────────────────┐  ┌─────────────────┐ │\n51: │  │   Clientset     │  │    Informers    │  │    Listers      │ │\n52: │  │                 │  │                 │  │                 │ │\n53: │  │ · Interface     │  │ · SharedInformer│  │ · Lister        │ │\n54: │  │ · Create/Get/...│  │   Factory       │  │ · NamespaceList │ │\n55: │  └─────────────────┘  │ · Per-type      │  └─────────────────┘ │\n56: │                       │   informers     │                      │\n57: │                       └─────────────────┘                      │\n58: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n59: ```\n60: \n61: ### Component Interactions\n62: \n63: 1. **Type Definitions** (`codeinterpreter_types.go`): Go structs with kubebuilder markers\n64: 2. **Scheme Registration** (`register.go`): Adds types to the runtime scheme\n65: 3. **Code Generation**: `controller-gen` generates DeepCopy methods; `code-generator` creates client-go\n66: 4. **Client Consumers**: Workload Manager, CLI tools, external controllers\n67: \n68: ---\n69: \n70: ## Data Structures\n71: \n72: ### Core Types\n73: \n74: #### CodeInterpreterPhase\n75: \n76: Enumeration representing the lifecycle phases of a CodeInterpreter.\n77: \n78: ```go\n79: // CodeInterpreterPhase represents the current phase of a CodeInterpreter.\n80: // +kubebuilder:validation:Enum=Pending;Running;Succeeded;Failed\n81: // +kubebuilder:validation:Type=string\n82: type CodeInterpreterPhase string\n83: \n84: const (\n85:     // CodeInterpreterPhasePending indicates the interpreter is being provisioned.\n86:     CodeInterpreterPhasePending CodeInterpreterPhase = \"Pending\"\n87: \n88:     // CodeInterpreterPhaseRunning indicates the interpreter is active and ready.\n89:     CodeInterpreterPhaseRunning CodeInterpreterPhase = \"Running\"\n90: \n91:     // CodeInterpreterPhaseSucceeded indicates the interpreter completed successfully.\n92:     CodeInterpreterPhaseSucceeded CodeInterpreterPhase = \"Succeeded\"\n93: \n94:     // CodeInterpreterPhaseFailed indicates the interpreter failed.\n95:     CodeInterpreterPhaseFailed CodeInterpreterPhase = \"Failed\"\n96: )\n97: ```\n98: \n99: #### ProgrammingLanguage\n100: \n101: Enumeration of supported programming languages with validation.\n102: \n103: ```go\n104: // ProgrammingLanguage represents a supported programming language.\n105: // +kubebuilder:validation:Enum=python;javascript;typescript;go;rust;java;cpp\n106: // +kubebuilder:validation:Type=string\n107: type ProgrammingLanguage string\n108: \n109: const (\n110:     LanguagePython     ProgrammingLangu