: \n453: ### Error Categories\n454: \n455: | Category | Source | Handling Strategy |\n456: |----------|--------|-------------------|\n457: | Schema Validation | Kubebuilder markers | API server rejects with 422 |\n458: | Type Conversion | runtime.Object interface | Compile-time checking |\n459: | Serialization | JSON marshaling | Return error to caller |\n460: | Code Generation | controller-gen | CI/CD failure, fix and regenerate |\n461: \n462: ### Error Propagation\n463: \n464: ```go\n465: // Example error handling pattern for client usage\n466: func (c *CodeInterpreterClient) SafeCreate(ctx context.Context, ci *v1alpha1.CodeInterpreter) (*v1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, error) {\n467:     // Validate before sending\n468:     if err := validateCodeInterpreter(ci); err != nil {\n469:         return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"validation failed: %w\", err)\n470:     }\n471: \n472:     result, err := c.client.CodeInterpreters(ci.Namespace).Create(ctx, ci, metav1.CreateOptions{})\n473:     if err != nil {\n474:         // Check for specific Kubernetes errors\n475:         if apierrors.IsAlreadyExists(err) {\n476:             return nil, ErrCodeInterpreterExists\n477:         }\n478:         if apierrors.IsInvalid(err) {\n479:             return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"invalid spec: %w\", err)\n480:         }\n481:         return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"create failed: %w\", err)\n482:     }\n483: \n484:     return result, nil\n485: }\n486: ```\n487: \n488: ---\n489: \n490: ## Testing Strategy\n491: \n492: ### Unit Tests\n493: \n494: #### Type Definition Tests\n495: \n496: Located in `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types_test.go`:\n497: \n498: ```go\n499: func TestCodeInterpreterImplementsRuntimeObject(t *testing.T) {\n500:     ci := &CodeInterpreter{}\n501:     var _ runtime.Object = ci // Compile-time assertion\n502: }\n503: \n504: func TestCodeInterpreterListImplementsRuntimeObject(t *testing.T) {\n505:     list := &CodeInterpreterList{}\n506:     var _ runtime.Object = list // Compile-time assertion\n507: }\n508: \n509: func TestCodeInterpreterDeepCopy(t *testing.T) {\n510:     original := &CodeInterpreter{\n511:         Spec: CodeInterpreterSpec{\n512:             Image:    \"python:3.11\",\n513:             Language: LanguagePython,\n514:             TimeoutSeconds: func() *int32 { i := int32(300); return &i }(),\n515:         },\n516:     }\n517: \n518:     copied := original.DeepCopy()\n519: \n520:     // Verify copy is independent\n521:     *copied.Spec.TimeoutSeconds = 600\n522:     assert.Equal(t, int32(300), *original.Spec.TimeoutSeconds)\n523: }\n524: \n525: func TestProgrammingLanguageValidation(t *testing.T) {\n526:     validLanguages := []ProgrammingLanguage{\n527:         LanguagePython, LanguageJavaScript, LanguageTypeScript,\n528:         LanguageGo, LanguageRust, LanguageJava, LanguageCpp,\n529:     }\n530: \n531:     for _, lang := range validLanguages {\n532:         assert.NotEmpty(t, lang)\n533:     }\n534: }\n535: ```\n536: \n537: ### Integration Tests\n538: \n539: #### Scheme Registration Test\n540: \n541: ```go\n542: func TestCodeInterpreterSchemeRegistration(t *testing.T) {\n543:     scheme := runtime.NewScheme()\n544:     err := v1alpha1.AddToScheme(scheme)\n545:     require.NoError(t, err)\n546: \n547:     // Verify CodeInterpreter is registered\n548:     gv := v1alpha1.SchemeGroupVersion\n549:     gvk := gv.WithKind(\"CodeInterpreter\")\n550:     obj, err := scheme.New(gvk)\n551:     require.NoError(t, err)\n552:     assert.IsType(t, &v1alpha1.CodeInterpreter{}, obj)\n553: }\n554: ```\n555: \n556: ### Code Generation Verification\n557: \n558: ```bash\n559: #!/bin/bash\n560: # verify-codegen.sh\n561: \n562: # Generate code\n563: make generate\n564: \n565: # Verify compilation\n566: go build ./pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/...\n567: \n568: # Verify tests pass\n569: go test ./pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/...\n570: \n571: # Check no uncommitted changes\n572: if [[ -n $(git status --porcelain pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/zz_generated.deepcopy.go) ]]; then\n573:     echo \"ERROR: DeepCopy methods not up to date\"\n574:     exit 1\n575: fi\n576: ```\n577: \n578: ### Test Coverage Requirements\n579: \n580: | Component | Coverage Target |\n581: |-----------|-----------------|\n582: | Type definitions | 80%+ (struct validation) |\n583: | DeepCopy methods | Verified via generated code |\n584: | Scheme registration | 100% |\n585: | Client interfaces | Mock-based unit tests |\n586: \n587: ### Continuous Integration\n588: \n589: ```yaml\n590: # .github/workflows/test.yaml\n591: name: Test\n592: \n593: on: [push, pull_request]\n594: \n595: jobs:\n596:   test:\n597:     runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n598:     steps:\n599:       - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n600: \n601:       - name: Set up Go\n602:         uses: actions/setup-go@v5\n603:         with:\n604:           go-version: '1.24'\n605: \n606:       - name: Verify code generation\n607:         run: make verify-generate\n608: \n609:       - name: Build\n610:         run: go build ./pkg/apis/...\n611: \n612:       - name: Test\n613:         run: go test -v -race ./pkg/apis/...\n614: \n615:       - name: Lint\n616:         uses: golangci/golangci-lint-action@v6\n617:         with:\n618:           version: latest\n619: ```\n620: \n621: ---\n622: \n623: ## File Layout\n624: \n625: ```\n626: pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/\n627: ├── codeinterpreter_types.go      # CodeInterpreter type definitions (NEW)\n628: ├── agentruntime_types.go         # AgentRuntime type definitions (existing)\n629: ├── register.go                   # Scheme registration (MODIFIED)\n630: ├── doc.go                        # Package documentation\n631: ├── zz_generated.deepcopy.go      # Generated DeepCopy methods (GENERATED)\n632: └── codeinterpreter_types_test.go # Unit tests (NEW)\n633: ```\n634: \n635: ---\n636: \n637: ## Dependencies\n638: \n639: | Dependency | Version | Purpose |\n640: |------------|---------|---------|\n641: | `k8s.io/apimachinery` | `v0.34.1` | TypeMeta, ObjectMeta, runtime.Object |\n642: | `k8s.io/api/core/v1` | `v0.34.1` | ResourceRequirements, EnvVar, SecurityContext |\n643: | `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/api/resource` | `v0.34.1` | Quantity for storage sizes |\n644: | `sigs.k8s.io/controller-tools` | `v0.17.2` | controller-gen for code generation |\n645: | `k8s.io/code-generator` | `v0.34.1` | client-go generation |\n646: \n647: ---\n648: \n649: ## Design Decisions\n650: \n651: ### 1. Separate CRD vs Extending AgentRuntime\n652: \n653: **Decision**: Create a separate `CodeInterpreter` CRD rather than extending `AgentRuntime`.\n654: \n655: **Rationale**:\n656: - CodeInterpreter has distinct lifecycle semantics focused on code execution\n657: - Independent RBAC and scheduling policies\n658: - Client-go library explicitly defines separate interfaces (`CodeInterpretersGetter` vs `AgentRuntimesGetter`)\n659: - Supports language-specific optimizations and security policies\n660: \n661: ### 2. Controlled API Surface\n662: \n663: **Decision**: Define focused fields (`Image`, `Language`, `Resources`, `TimeoutSeconds`, etc.) rather than embedding full `PodSpec`.\n664: \n665: **Rationale**:\n666: - Guides users toward code execution best practices\n667: - Simplifies API surface\n668: - Enables language-specific validation and defaults\n669: - Maintains consistency with `AgentRuntime` pattern\n670: \n671: ### 3. Namespaced Scope\n672: \n673: **Decision**: CRD scope is `Namespaced`.\n674: \n675: **Rationale**:\n676: - Aligns with multi-tenant Kubernetes patterns\n677: - Enables namespace-level quotas and isolation\n678: - Consistent with `AgentRuntime` scope\n679: \n680: ### 4. Status Subresource\n681: \n682: **Decision**: Enable status subresource with `+kubebuilder:subresource:status`.\n683: \n684: **Rationale**:\n685: - Separation of concerns between spec and status\n686: - Enables RBAC to allow status updates without full object access\n687: - Standard Kubernetes pattern for controllers\n688: \n689: ---\n690: \n691: ## References\n692: \n693: - [Kubernetes Custom Resources](https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/extend-kubernetes/api-extension/custom-resources/)\n694: - [Kubebuilder CRD Markers](https://book.kubebuilder.io/reference/markers/crd.html)\n695: - [Code Generator](https://github.com/kubernetes/code-generator)\n696: - [client-go](https://github.com/kubernetes/client-go)\n697: \n698: ---\n699: \n700: ## Change Log\n701: \n702: | Version | Date | Changes |\n703: |---------|------|---------|\n704: | 1.0 | 2026-04-11 | Initial design for AR-002 CodeInterpreter CRD |\n\n(End of file - total 704 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-002 Design: CRD CodeInterpreter Type Definition\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-002  \n**Module:** `pkg/apis`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** Small  \n\nDefine the Go type definitions for the `CodeInterpreter` Custom Resource Definition (CRD) under the API group `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`. The CodeInterpreter CRD represents a specialized sandbox for executing code snippets safely within Kubernetes.\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\n### High-Level Design\n\nThe CodeInterpreter type extends the existing `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` API group alongside `AgentRuntime`, sharing the same scheme registration and code generation pipeline.\n\n```","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/design.md","time":{"start":1775841547719,"end":1775841547739}}}}
