{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775841580841,"sessionID":"ses_28798c033ffeiLKSjmHjP0bQ2x","part":{"id":"prt_d78681727001ZTEUzkGo5hQGbX","messageID":"msg_d7867d72c001TRjcjONPwMIAYL","sessionID":"ses_28798c033ffeiLKSjmHjP0bQ2x","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1775841588210,"sessionID":"ses_28798c033ffeiLKSjmHjP0bQ2x","part":{"id":"prt_d78682c750012NJOr37JSrpsLP","messageID":"msg_d7867d72c001TRjcjONPwMIAYL","sessionID":"ses_28798c033ffeiLKSjmHjP0bQ2x","type":"text","text":"Now I have a clear understanding of the project. I can see that AR-003 is about extracting shared types and constants that are currently in `codeinterpreter_types.go` (like `ProtocolType`, `TargetPort`) into a dedicated shared types file that can be used by both `AgentRuntime` and `CodeInterpreter` CRDs.\n\nLet me write the proposal.md:","time":{"start":1775841588207,"end":1775841588207}}}
