{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775841667480,"sessionID":"ses_28798c033ffeiLKSjmHjP0bQ2x","part":{"id":"prt_d786833f1001jGbGZtA6YsOA4v","messageID":"msg_d7867d72c001TRjcjONPwMIAYL","sessionID":"ses_28798c033ffeiLKSjmHjP0bQ2x","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:12","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md","content":"# AgentCube CRD Type Definitions\n\nThis proposal defines the Custom Resource Definition (CRD) types for the AgentCube project.\n\n---\n\n# AR-003 — CRD Shared Types and Constants\n\n## Purpose\n\nExtract and consolidate shared types, constants, and common structures used by both `AgentRuntime` and `CodeInterpreter` CRDs into a dedicated `shared_types.go` file in `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1`. This work eliminates code duplication, ensures consistency across CRD types, and establishes a single source of truth for common API primitives like network protocols, port definitions, and sandbox templates.\n\n## Scope\n\n### In scope\n\n| Item | Detail |\n|------|--------|\n| **Package** | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1` |\n| **API group** | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` (existing) |\n| **Version** | `v1alpha1` (existing) |\n| **Types defined** | `ProtocolType`, `TargetPort`, `SandboxTemplate`, `SandboxPhase`, `ConditionType`, `CommonCondition` |\n| **Constants defined** | Protocol constants (`ProtocolHTTP`, `ProtocolHTTPS`), Phase constants, Common condition type constants |\n| **Kubebuilder markers** | `+k8s:deepcopy-gen`, validation markers (`+kubebuilder:validation:Enum`, `+kubebuilder:default`, etc.) |\n| **Code generation** | `controller-gen object` → updates `zz_generated.deepcopy.go` with shared types |\n\n### Out of scope\n\n- Changes to `AgentRuntime` or `CodeInterpreter` specific types (those remain in their respective files)\n- New CRD definitions\n- Workload Manager HTTP API changes\n- Controller/reconciler logic changes\n- Helm chart modifications\n- client-go generation (consumes types, doesn't define them)\n\n## Design\n\n### File layout\n\n| File | Role |\n|------|------|\n| `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/shared_types.go` | **NEW** — Shared types, constants, and common structures |\n| `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/zz_generated.deepcopy.go` | **GENERATED** — DeepCopy methods for shared types (appended) |\n\n### Type definitions\n\n**`ProtocolType`** — Shared protocol enumeration:\n\n```go\n// ProtocolType represents the protocol for a target port.\n// +kubebuilder:validation:Enum=HTTP;HTTPS;TCP;UDP\n// +kubebuilder:validation:Type=string\ntype ProtocolType string\n\nconst (\n    // ProtocolHTTP represents the HTTP protocol.\n    ProtocolHTTP ProtocolType = \"HTTP\"\n\n    // ProtocolHTTPS represents the HTTPS protocol.\n    ProtocolHTTPS ProtocolType = \"HTTPS\"\n\n    // ProtocolTCP represents the raw TCP protocol.\n    ProtocolTCP ProtocolType = \"TCP\"\n\n    // ProtocolUDP represents the UDP protocol.\n    ProtocolUDP ProtocolType = \"UDP\"\n)\n```\n\n**`TargetPort`** — Shared port definition structure:\n\n```go\n// TargetPort defines a port to expose from the sandbox container.\n// This is used to configure entry points for accessing the sandbox.\ntype TargetPort struct {\n    // PathPrefix is an optional URL path prefix for this port.\n    // Used primarily for HTTP/HTTPS protocols.\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n    PathPrefix string `json:\"pathPrefix,omitempty\"`\n\n    // Name is an optional name for this port.\n    // If specified, this name can be used to reference the port.\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Pattern=`^[a-z0-9]([-a-z0-9]*[a-z0-9])?$`\n    Name string `json:\"name,omitempty\"`\n\n    // Port is the port number to expose.\n    // This field is required.\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Minimum=1\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Maximum=65535\n    Port int32 `json:\"port\"`\n\n    // Protocol is the protocol for this port.\n    // Defaults to HTTP if not specified.\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n    // +kubebuilder:default=\"HTTP\"\n    Protocol ProtocolType `json:\"protocol,omitempty\"`\n\n    // TargetPort is the port to access on the pods targeted by the service.\n    // Defaults to the Port value if not specified.\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Minimum=1\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Maximum=65535\n    TargetPort int32 `json:\"targetPort,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n**`SandboxTemplate`** — Shared sandbox template structure:\n\n```go\n// SandboxTemplate defines the template for creating a sandbox.\n// It contains the Pod specification and optional metadata.\n// This template is used by both AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter to define\n// the underlying sandbox pod configuration.\ntype SandboxTemplate struct {\n    // Labels are optional labels to apply to the sandbox pod.\n    // These labels will be merged with any system-generated labels.\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n    // +mapType=atomic\n    Labels map[string]string `json:\"labels,omitempty\"`\n\n    // Annotations are optional annotations to apply to the sandbox pod.\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n    // +mapType=atomic\n    Annotations map[string]string `json:\"annotations,omitempty\"`\n\n    // Spec is the Pod specification for the sandbox.\n    // This field is required and defines the container(s) to run.\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n    Spec corev1.PodSpec `json:\"spec\"`\n}\n```\n\n**`SandboxPhase`** — Shared lifecycle phase enumeration:\n\n```go\n// SandboxPhase represents the current phase of a sandbox resource.\n// This is used by both AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter to indicate lifecycle state.\n// +kubebuilder:validation:Enum=Pending;Creating;Running;Terminating;Succeeded;Failed;Unknown\n// +kubebuilder:validation:Type=string\ntype SandboxPhase string\n\nconst (\n    // SandboxPhasePending indicates the sandbox is pending creation.\n    SandboxPhasePending SandboxPhase = \"Pending\"\n\n    // SandboxPhaseCreating indicates the sandbox is being created.\n    SandboxPhaseCreating SandboxPhase = \"Creating\"\n\n    // SandboxPhaseRunning indicates the sandbox is active and running.\n    SandboxPhaseRunning SandboxPhase = \"Running\"\n\n    // SandboxPhaseTerminating indicates the sandbox is being terminated.\n    SandboxPhaseTerminating SandboxPhase = \"Terminating\"\n\n    // SandboxPhaseSucceeded indicates the sandbox completed successfully.\n    SandboxPhaseSucceeded SandboxPhase = \"Succeeded\"\n\n    // SandboxPhaseFailed indicates the sandbox failed.\n    SandboxPhaseFailed SandboxPhase = \"Failed\"\n\n    // SandboxPhaseUnknown indicates the sandbox state is unknown.\n    SandboxPhaseUnknown SandboxPhase = \"Unknown\"\n)\n```\n\n**`ConditionType`** — Shared condition type constants:\n\n```go\n// CommonConditionType represents condition types shared across sandbox resources.\n// +kubebuilder:validation:Enum=Ready;Initialized;SandboxCreated;SandboxReady;Failed;Terminating\n// +kubebuilder:validation:Type=string\ntype CommonConditionType string\n\nconst (\n    // CommonConditionReady indicates the resource is ready to accept requests.\n    CommonConditionReady CommonConditionType = \"Ready\"\n\n    // CommonConditionInitialized indicates the resource has been initialized.\n    CommonConditionInitialized CommonConditionType = \"Initialized\"\n\n    // CommonConditionSandboxCreated indicates the sandbox has been created.\n    CommonConditionSandboxCreated CommonConditionType = \"SandboxCreated\"\n\n    // CommonConditionSandboxReady indicates the sandbox is ready for use.\n    CommonConditionSandboxReady CommonConditionType = \"SandboxReady\"\n\n    // CommonConditionFailed indicates the resource has failed.\n    CommonConditionFailed CommonConditionType = \"Failed\"\n\n    // CommonConditionTerminating indicates the resource is being terminated.\n    CommonConditionTerminating CommonConditionType = \"Terminating\"\n)\n```\n\n**`CommonCondition`** — Shared condition structure:\n\n```go\n// CommonCondition represents a condition of a sandbox resource.\n// This structure is shared by AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter for status reporting.\ntype CommonCondition struct {\n    // Type is the type of the condition.\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n    Type CommonConditionType `json:\"type\"`\n\n    // Status is the status of the condition (True, False, Unknown).\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Enum=True;False;Unknown\n    Status corev1.ConditionStatus `json:\"status\"`\n\n    // LastTransitionTime is the last time the condition transitioned.\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n    LastTransitionTime metav1.Time `json:\"lastTransitionTime,omitempty\"`\n\n    // Reason is a brief reason for the condition's last transition.\n    // This is typically a CamelCase string.\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n    Reason string `json:\"reason,omitempty\"`\n\n    // Message is a human-readable message indicating details about the transition.\n    // +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n    Message string `json:\"message,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n### Import requirements\n\nThe shared types file requires these imports:\n\n```go\nimport (\n    corev1 \"k8s.io/api/core/v1\"\n    metav1 \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\"\n)\n```\n\n### Code generation pipeline\n\n```\ncontroller-gen object → pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/zz_generated.deepcopy.go (appends shared types)\n```\n\nInvocation: `make generate` or `make gen-all`\n\n### Refactoring impact on existing types\n\nAfter creating `shared_types.go`, the following refactorings will be applied:\n\n| File | Change |\n|------|--------|\n| `codeinterpreter_types.go` | Remove `ProtocolType`, `ProtocolHTTP`, `ProtocolHTTPS`, `TargetPort`, `CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate` (use shared types instead) |\n| `agentruntime_types.go` | Optionally adopt `TargetPort` and `SandboxTemplate` for consistency |\n\n**Note**: The actual refactoring of existing files is outside the scope of this AR; this AR only creates the shared types file. Subsequent ARs will handle the refactoring.\n\n## Impact analysis\n\n### Files created\n\n| File | Lines (est.) |\n|------|-------------|\n| `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/shared_types.go` | ~180 |\n\n### Files generated (not hand-edited)\n\n| File | Tool |\n|------|------|\n| `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/zz_generated.deepcopy.go` (appended) | `controller-gen object` |\n\n### Downstream consumers\n\n| Consumer | Dependency |\n|----------|-----------|\n| `AgentRuntime` types | Can import `TargetPort`, `SandboxTemplate`, `SandboxPhase`, `CommonCondition` |\n| `CodeInterpreter` types | Can import `TargetPort`, `SandboxTemplate`, `SandboxPhase`, `CommonCondition` (replacing current definitions) |\n| `client-go` typed client | Will have DeepCopy methods for shared types |\n| Controllers | Can use shared condition types and phase constants |\n\n### Breaking change risk\n\n- **None**: This is a new file with no changes to existing APIs.\n- **Future**: When existing types are refactored to use shared types, that will be a breaking change managed in separate ARs.\n- **Compatibility**: All shared types are additive and do not modify existing field names or structures.\n\n## Alternatives considered\n\n### 1. Keep types duplicated in each CRD file\n\n**Approach**: Maintain separate `ProtocolType`, `TargetPort`, etc. in both `agentruntime_types.go` and `codeinterpreter_types.go`.\n\n**Rejected because**: Code duplication leads to maintenance overhead and potential inconsistencies. Changes to port definitions would need to be made in multiple places. The current `codeinterpreter_types.go` already defines these, and `AgentRuntime` may need similar structures in the future.\n\n### 2. Create a separate API group for shared types\n\n**Approach**: Create a new API group `shared.agentcube.volcano.sh` or `core.agentcube.volcano.sh` for shared types.\n\n**Rejected because**: Overkill for a small set of shared types. Having shared types in the same `v1alpha1` package simplifies imports and keeps the API surface cohesive. Separate API groups would require additional scheme registration and client generation complexity.\n\n### 3. Use Kubernetes native types exclusively\n\n**Approach**: Use `corev1.Protocol` instead of defining `ProtocolType`, use `corev1.ContainerPort` instead of `TargetPort`.\n\n**Rejected because**: AgentCube needs domain-specific validation and defaults (e.g., defaulting to HTTP, supporting only HTTP/HTTPS for now). Native types are too broad and don't allow for custom kubebuilder validation markers specific to AgentCube's use case.\n\n### 4. Embed shared types as inline structs\n\n**Approach**: Define shared structures as inline anonymous structs within each CRD spec.\n\n**Rejected because**: Prevents code reuse and makes it impossible to define common utility functions or methods that work with these types. Also complicates code generation for DeepCopy methods.\n\n## Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Version | Purpose |\n|------------|---------|---------|\n| `k8s.io/api/core/v1` | `v0.34.1` | `corev1.PodSpec`, `corev1.ConditionStatus` |\n| `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1` | `v0.34.1` | `metav1.Time` |\n| `controller-gen` | `v0.17.2` | DeepCopy generation for shared types |\n\n## Verification\n\n```bash\n# Generate DeepCopy methods (includes shared types)\nmake generate\n\n# Verify compilation\ngo build ./pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/...\n\n# Run tests\ngo test ./pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/...\n\n# Verify no diff (all generated files committed)\nmake gen-check\n\n# Verify shared types can be imported and used\ngo vet ./pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/...\n```\n\n## References\n\n- [AR-001](#ar-001--crd-agentruntime-type-definition) — AgentRuntime CRD types\n- [AR-002](#ar-002--crd-codeinterpreter-type-definition) — CodeInterpreter CRD types\n- [Kubernetes Custom Resources](https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/extend-kubernetes/api-extension/custom-resources/)\n- [Kubebuilder CRD Markers](https://book.kubebuilder.io/reference/markers/crd.html)\n\n---\n\n*AR-003 — Module: pkg/apis — Language: Go — Size: S*\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime_types.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/register.go":[]},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775841667408,"end":1775841667477}}}}
